OneToOneMappedThesaurus - Class in ie.gmit.dip
OneToOneMappedThesaurus is a concrete class which implements the Thesaurable interface.
OneToOneMappedThesaurus() - Constructor for class ie.gmit.dip.OneToOneMappedThesaurus
Simple constructor method.
OneToOneMappedThesaurus(HashMap<String, String>) - Constructor for class ie.gmit.dip.OneToOneMappedThesaurus
Constructor method which allows one to configure the HashMap words.
OneToOneMappedThesaurusBuilder - Class in ie.gmit.dip
OneToOneMappedThesaurusBuilder is a concrete class which is used to construct a OneToOneMappedThesaurus from a pair of files, one file containing a thesaurus of words, with synonyms entered as comma separated values on each line, and the other file containing a list of priority words to which words in the thesaurus should be mapped when said priority word is encountered in the thesaurus.
OneToOneMappedThesaurusBuilder() - Constructor for class ie.gmit.dip.OneToOneMappedThesaurusBuilder
Simple constructor which instantiates instance variables and sets the default thesaurus and priority word file inputs.
OneToOneMappedThesaurusBuilder(File, File) - Constructor for class ie.gmit.dip.OneToOneMappedThesaurusBuilder
Overloaded constructor which allows the thesaurusFile and priorityWordSetFile locations to be defined.
Optionable - Interface in ie.gmit.dip
Optionable is an abstract interface which declares the functional behavior expected of an option which a user may wish to select or run.
